To print the numbers between 1 and 10 using a for loop in Java, you can write a simple program like this:

```java
public class Main {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Loop from 1 to 10
        for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++) {
            // Print the current number
            System.out.println(i);
        }
    }
}
```

Here's a breakdown of the code:

- `public class Main`: This declares a class named `Main`. In Java, all code must be inside a class.
- `public static void main(String[] args)`: This is the main method, which is the entry point for any Java application.
- `for (int i = 1; i <= 10; i++)`: This is a for loop that initializes `i` to 1, checks if `i` is less than or equal to 10, and increments `i` by 1 after each loop iteration.
- `System.out.println(i)`: This prints the current value of `i` to the console.

When you run this program, it will print the numbers 1 through 10, each on a new line.
